					<description><![CDATA[<p>Teaching AI to interact with the real world is one of the most complex challenges today. While chatbots thrived on internet text, robots need physical experience to learn. To solve</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ropedia-raises-30m-pre-a-funding-scale-physical-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ropedia Raises $30M in Pre-A Funding To Scale Physical AI Data Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Teaching AI to interact with the real world is one of the most complex challenges today. While chatbots thrived on internet text, robots need physical experience to learn. To solve this bottleneck, </span><a href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20260723509119/en/Ropedia-Raises-%2430-Million-to-Scale-Data-Infrastructure-for-Physical-AI" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Ropedia raises $30M</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> in Pre-A funding to expand its real-world interaction data platform for robotics. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This investment puts Ropedia at the core of the growing physical AI market. It will help the Singapore-based startup build a platform where robots can learn complex tasks like building electronics or handling tools.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Ropedia is Rethinking How Physical AI Learns</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203738" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203738" class="size-large wp-image-203738" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Ropedia-1024x341.jpeg" alt="A dark themed image showing Ropedia&apos;s goal of building the future of physical intelligence" width="1024" height="341" /><p id="caption-attachment-203738" class="wp-caption-text">Ropedia: Building the Future of Physical Intelligence</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ropedia was established in late 2025 by Zhaoxi Chen, Fangzhou Hong, and Ziwei Liu and is headquartered in Singapore and Mountain View, California. The team founders have rich research experience at Meta, Nanyang Technological University, and 3D computer vision.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They are pooling their knowledge to solve a key problem in physical AI learning. The traditional method of AI training is to use public websites for scraping. Physical AI demands something more. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Robots need to learn how to interpret tactile pressure, the angle of cameras, the positioning of the body and timing. They require actual sensory data, in synch, from human motion. Ropedia creates this raw data directly and does not just relabel preexisting datasets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s solution is 50 times less costly than a classic teleoperation setup for collecting data. Human collectors of natural interaction data are used in everyday environments, rather than installing costly robot equipment for each trial. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ropedia collects this information in its flagship dataset, Xperience-10M. More than 10,000 hours of multimodal recordings and 10 million interaction episodes already exist in this library. It provides robotics labs with structured loggings of real human actions for training.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/atoms-raises-1-7-billion-robotics-automation/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Atoms Raises $1.7 Billion To Automate Physical Industries</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The HOMIE Hardware Advantage</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203737" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203737" class="size-large wp-image-203737" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/homiedevice-featured-1024x665.jpg" alt="White halo-style head-mounted device with four integrated camera sensors and a rear swappable battery module, shown standalone and worn on a mannequin head against a black background." width="1024" height="665" /><p id="caption-attachment-203737" class="wp-caption-text">HOMIE Device. Ropedia</p></div>
<p><a href="https://ropedia-dev.com/blog/20251216_introducing_ropedia/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">HOMIE</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> is at the core of the Ropedia data engine. It is a proprietary wearable head-mounted device that captures multimodal streams at the same time. Additionally, HOMIE captures FPS video, audio, depth maps, hand tracking, gaze directions, body movements and camera poses while worn.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most importantly, all data streams in HOMIE get accurate timestamps. Physical AI models require that a system see, feel and act exactly the same at every millisecond. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, when it comes to sync, most capture tools that are currently available don’t work at this level. HOMIE solves this problem straight out of the box.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The lightweight, portable nature of the wearable makes it possible to be worn on a factory floor, in a kitchen, or in a repair shop by anyone. Ropedia has already started mass production of HOMIE to supply tech partners and commercial clients.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/genius-ai-raises-44-million-series-d-service-economy/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Genius AI Raises $44M Into AI In-Person Service Economy</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling Data Fleets Across Two Continents</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $30 million capital injection came through two Pre-A tranches. In mid-March 2026, it closed a strategic $8 million seed-stage round and a new $22 million round. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Individual angel investors, renowned AI researchers and enterprise tech and robotics partners supported the round. The new capital will fuel Ropedia’s expansion of data collection fleets in Southeast Asia and North America.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In additional, the startup will also increase the rate at which Ropedia deploys HOMIE to capture a wider range of &#8216;real-world&#8217; behaviors. Ropedia will also use some of the capital for strategic recruitment, especially of engineers at its Mountain View location. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ropedia’s data infrastructure is already supporting over a dozen North American AI companies to develop foundation models for autonomous systems. By capturing human action at scale, the startup provides the essential foundation robotics developers need to build smarter and more capable machines.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/crystalys-therapeutics-raises-130-million-gout-drug/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Crystalys Therapeutics Raises $130M for Gout Drug Push</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ropedia-raises-30m-pre-a-funding-scale-physical-ai-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ropedia Raises $30M in Pre-A Funding To Scale Physical AI Data Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
