					<description><![CDATA[<p>Travis Kalanick is making a loud return to the global tech stage with a bold vision for heavy industry. His physical AI startup Atoms raises $1.7 billion in a massive</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/atoms-raises-1-7-billion-robotics-automation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Uber Founder’s Robotics Company Atoms Raises $1.7 Billion To Automate Physical Industries</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Travis Kalanick is making a loud return to the global tech stage with a bold vision for heavy industry. His physical AI startup Atoms raises $1.7 billion in a massive funding round led by venture powerhouse Andreessen Horowitz. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The mega-investment consolidates a number of stealth operations and it also represents a new chapter in the life of the former Uber chief executive. Ben Horowitz joins the Atoms board, a bit of </span><a href="https://atoms.co/unfinished-business" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><i><span style="font-weight: 400">unfinished business</span></i></a> <span style="font-weight: 400">since Kalanick’s blog posting in 2011.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Atoms Is Targeting Heavy Industries Over Humanoid Robots</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203729" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203729" class="size-large wp-image-203729" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/ATOMS-1-1024x695.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="695" /><p id="caption-attachment-203729" class="wp-caption-text">Atoms Industrial AI</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Atoms centers its strategy on specialized, task-specific machinery rather than stylish humanoid designs. While many AI startups chase general-purpose humanoid robots, Kalanick’s firm believes industrial work requires purpose-built hardware. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company focuses squarely on capital-heavy physical sectors like mining, heavy transport, construction, and commercial food production. Kalanick views this move as the culmination of a decade-long shift from bits to physical atoms. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He describes these automated installations as atoms-based computers. In Kalanick’s view, heavy manufacturing functions as the processing unit, commercial real estate provides physical storage, and transport logistics operate as the core network. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The objective is clear. Atoms wants to digitize and automate critical supply chain tasks that pure software can never handle alone.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/genius-ai-raises-44-million-series-d-service-economy/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Genius AI Raises $44M To Into AI In-Person Service Economy</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Unifying Three Core Operating Divisions</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round unifies three separate operational divisions under one consolidated equity structure. The first, Atoms Food, brings together Kalanick’s previous ghost-kitchen enterprise CloudKitchens.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The food division incorporates automated cooking platforms like Lab37 and software systems like Otter. Atoms Mining, the second division, focuses on autonomous heavy machinery in remote extraction sites. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This effort builds directly on Atoms’ recent acquisition of Pronto, an autonomous equipment company founded by former Uber engineer Anthony Levandowski. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Atoms Transport, the third division, operates as a flexible wheelbase for industrial robotics. It helps move goods across complex logistics hubs. Together, these three divisions create a comprehensive stack for automating physical production from the ground up.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/crystalys-therapeutics-raises-130-million-gout-drug/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Crystalys Therapeutics Raises $130M for Gout Drug Push</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Deep Investor Support and Uber’s Return</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $1.7 billion investment reflects strong confidence from major venture capital players. Joining lead investor Andreessen Horowitz are prominent firms like Bain Capital, Fifth Wall, K5 Global, Abstract, Chemistry, A*, and SV Angel.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most surprisingly, Uber was a direct equity investor. With the backing, Kalanick is completing a full circle with the ride-hailing firm he helped found in 2009 and left in 2017. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In addition to equity, Atoms also landed large debt facilities from big financial institutions such as JPMorgan, Goldman Sachs, Bank of America, Wells Fargo and Barclays, giving the company huge debt leverage to fund heavy hardware.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Atoms will use the $1.7 billion infusion of cash to ramp up the pace of machine assembly, to increase its deployments out in the field and to attract top engineering talent. Labor shortages and costs are increasingly becoming a challenge for global supply chains, and there is a strong demand for reliable, automated physical systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Specialized industrial machines are much better suited to working in tough environments than humanoid robots, Ben Horowitz highlighted. Atoms is all about physical AI by prioritizing work over consumer tech. The company hopes to demonstrate that digitalization of physical work will propel the next industrial revolution.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/candid-health-raises-120m-ai-revenue-cycle-management/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Candid Health Raises $120M for AI Healthcare Revenue Platform</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/atoms-raises-1-7-billion-robotics-automation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Uber Founder’s Robotics Company Atoms Raises $1.7 Billion To Automate Physical Industries</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
