					<description><![CDATA[<p>The in-person service economy has seen a massive surge in the adoption of artificial intelligence. Tech startup Genius AI raises $44 million to capitalize on this growth. The Series D</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/genius-ai-raises-44-million-series-d-service-economy/" data-wpel-link="internal">Genius AI Raises $44 Million To Expand From Wellness Into AI In-Person Service Economy</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The in-person service economy has seen a massive surge in the adoption of artificial intelligence. Tech startup </span><a href="https://genius.ai/blog/your-genius-is-the-craft" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400">Genius AI raises $44 million</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> to capitalize on this growth. The Series D funding now gives Genius AI, formerly GlossGenius, a $1.15 billion valuation. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Led by venture capital firm Lux Capital. Other participating investors include Bessemer Venture Partners, Imaginary Ventures, L Catterton Growth, 2048 Ventures, and StepStone Private Ventures. The funding will help Genius AI pivot from beauty booking software toward autonomous AI tools for the broader in-person service economy.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Genius AI is Rebranding Beyond Beauty and Wellness</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203718" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203718" class="size-large wp-image-203718" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Danielle-and-Leah-Cohen-Shohet-1024x643.jpg" alt="Identical twin sisters and Genius AI co-founders Danielle and Leah Cohen-Shohet posing back-to-back with folded arms against a neutral studio backdrop." width="1024" height="643" /><p id="caption-attachment-203718" class="wp-caption-text">Danielle and Leah Cohen-Shohet. Credit: Genius AI</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Danielle and Leah Cohen-Shohet, identical twin sisters, launched Genius AI (then GlossGenius) in 2015. They built GlossGenius to help salon owners, aestheticians and spa operators manage their daily work. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Danielle taught herself computer programming to write the initial codebase. Over the years, the software grew into a dominant market force. It helped small operators process payments, take appointments, and market their services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Now, the company is changing its name to Genius AI. This rebrand signals a wider mission. As Genius AI, the company will support all physical service professionals. The platform will be used in physical therapy practices, medical spas, fitness studios, chiropractors, and health clinics.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates:</i></b> <a href="https://ventureburn.com/crystalys-therapeutics-raises-130-million-gout-drug/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Crystalys Therapeutics Raises $130M for Gout Drug Push</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Building Autonomous AI for Local Businesses</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The physical service economy in the United States includes roughly eight million businesses. They generate $2 trillion+ in annual consumer spending. Although </span><a href="https://www.timeetc.com/resources/how-to-achieve-more/the-big-price-of-small-tasks-how-entrepreneurs-may-be-unwittingly-keeping-their-businesses-small" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">research</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> shows that business owners spend nearly 36% of their work week dealing with back-office tasks. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Time with clients is often lost to paperwork, scheduling and late-night messages. Genius AI wants to eliminate that administrative burden completely. The platform is moving beyond simple assistant tools. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Genius AI is becoming an autonomous AI agent. The platform is to have agents that can carry out complex tasks end-to-end. The administrative tasks will be handled by the agents, leaving business owners with more time to meet their clients. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“The best work happens with a true partner beside you,” said Leah Cohen-Shohet, co-founder and chief business officer. “As identical twins, we grew up with that—someone who understands you and makes you better. That’s what we want for every owner.”</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/candid-health-raises-120m-ai-revenue-cycle-management/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Candid Health Raises $120M for AI Healthcare Revenue Platform</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Impressive Growth and Healthcare Expansion</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_203719" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203719" class="size-large wp-image-203719" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Genius-AI-raise-44M-1024x576.jpeg" alt="Graphic featuring the Genius AI logo in metallic lettering over a central card reading &apos;Series D $1.15B valuation&apos; surrounded by floating mobile app screenshots of AI administrative workflows." width="1024" height="576" /><p id="caption-attachment-203719" class="wp-caption-text">Funding Announcement. Credit: Genius AI</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company already boasts strong financial numbers and operational scale. More than 125,000 businesses across half of all U.S. ZIP codes currently use the system. Genius AI reports that its platform is approaching a $200 million annual revenue run-rate. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its tools have saved clients over 112 million hours of administrative work to date. To push deeper into health services, the company has added full HIPAA compliance to its platform. This regulatory approval lets physical therapists and clinical operators hold sensitive patient data safely. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It gives Genius AI a sharp advantage over traditional software tools that lack privacy protections. As artificial intelligence automates digital desk jobs, hands-on human care becomes far more valuable. Skilled specialists like trainers, massage therapists, and clinicians offer care that computer code cannot duplicate. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Genius AI plans to use its new capital to expand software development and scale its engineering team. The team believes the future of local business relies on smart automation that stays out of the way.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Updates: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/humanoid-raises-152m-series-a-uk-robotics-unicorn/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>Humanoid Raises $152 Million in Series A</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/genius-ai-raises-44-million-series-d-service-economy/" data-wpel-link="internal">Genius AI Raises $44 Million To Expand From Wellness Into AI In-Person Service Economy</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
